    <!-- Poem -->
    <div class="poem">
        The train exhales me<br>
        a huff of bodies spill out the doors<br><br>

        I climb the stairs in twos<br>
        reach for my bag<br>
        but grasp only air<br><br>

        Shit!<br>
        Lost bag<br>
        I run, but the train outruns me<br>
        So I stop<br>
        I weep<br><br>

        I am a child again.<br>
        I must be supervised<br>
        Tie a string around my wrist <br>
        yank me back<br><br>

        Go away! Go away!<br>
        I say to the normal adult who comes near<br>
        You mustn’t love me!<br><br>

        I lose things <br>
        miss things<br>
        and I’m embarrassed because<br>
        I’m not a real person yet.<br><br>

        I perform this plea dramatically <br>
        for no one in particular<br><br>

        And in this fantasy <br>
        Mr. No One doesn’t move at all<br>
        He only stands <br>
        looks at me, and says<br>
        C’mon!<br>
        Let’s find that bag.
    </div>
